                    <h3><a href="#">Sankashti Chaturthi</a></h3>
                    <div class="festival-para">
                    <p><strong>Sankashti Chaturthi</strong> is one of the most revered festivals in Hinduism, dedicated to Lord Ganesha, the deity known for removing obstacles, bestowing wisdom, and guiding devotees through life's challenges. As the first deity to be worshipped before any new venture or auspicious occasion, Lord Ganesha occupies a significant place in Hindu rituals and beliefs. He is affectionately referred to as "Vighnaharta" (the remover of obstacles) and "Sankatmochan" (the one who alleviates difficulties).</p>
                    <p>The term <strong>Sankashti</strong> is derived from the Sanskrit word meaning "deliverance from troubled times." It symbolizes the divine intervention of Lord Ganesha in times of distress, guiding devotees toward a path of peace, prosperity, and fulfillment. Observing the fast on Sankashti Chaturthi is believed to rid individuals of obstacles, cleanse negative karma, and pave the way for success in all endeavors.</p>
